 Miandad vote for India
Karachi: Pakistans former captain Zaheer Abbas believes the disappointing Test and one-day series loss to South Africa at home has dented the morale of the side ahead of the tour to India. We had a wonderful opportunity to win the match and series and get a big stepping stone for the India series. But the players displayed a non-serious attitude, he claimed. Another former captain, Javed Miandad also lashed out at the selectors for not having the courage to try out new players and depend on the same old lot for the tour to India. The former coach said India would start favourites in the one-day and Test series. Miandad said the inconsistent selection policies of the selection committee had led to the defeats to South Africa.  (PTI) 
